article.headline: UT-Chattanooga 24, Liberty 21
article.story:
LYNCHBURG, Va. (AP) -- Esteban Lopez kicked a 29-yard field goal
with no time left to give Chattanooga a 24-21 win over Liberty
Saturday.

Eldra Buckley ran in a 1-yard touchdown with 2:13 left in the
game to tie it at 21 apiece. Buckley carried the ball 21 times for
111 yards and ran for 28 yards for Chattanooga (3-3).

Lironnie Davis caught a 9-yard pass for a touchdown and ran it
20 yards for another. Davis finished with 98 yards rushing and 48
receiving. Antonio Miller finished 21-for-35 for 179 yards and one
interception.

Zach Terrell, who rushed for 241 yards, scored on a 3-yard run
and a 6-yard run for Liberty (1-5).

Chris Luck caught an 11-yard pass for a touchdown in the fourth.
Brook Farrel was 13 for 25 for 112 yards.
